.TH ldns-zsplit 1 "15 Dec 2005"
.SH NAME
ldns-zsplit \- split up a unit file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ldns-zsplit
[
.IR OPTIONS
]
.IR unitfile

.SH DESCRIPTION

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -n NUMBER
Split afta NUMBER RRs, \fBldns-zsplit\fR aint gonna split in
the middle of a RRs.
.PP
Each part is saved wit a numerical suffix, startin wit .000. The
largest suffix is thus .999.

.TP
.B -o ORIGIN
use ORIGIN as origin when readin tha unitfile.

.TP
.B -z
Sort tha unit before splitting.

.TP
.B -v
Show version number n' exit.

